{"url": "https://www.reddit.com/r/learnprogramming/comments/9ca76r/eli5_what_exactly_does_apache_zookeeper_do_and/", "text": "As title says, Im confused about what exactly zookeeper does, how the z nodes of zookeeper are related to data nodes of Hadoop. How would you use Zookeepr in conjunction with Hadoop (any simple example would do) Thanks.", "score": 15, "comments": [{"body": "the tl;dr is that zookeeper is a distributed robust tree intended to hold small pieces of data. it's supposed to be pretty much the last service to go down if your cluster goes fubar\n\ncommon usecases for zookeeper are service discovery, leader election and config storage\n\nso for hdfs, zookeeper knows which one is the active name node if you have a hot standby HA. see https://www.cloudera.com/documentation/enterprise/5-8-x/topics/cdh_hag_hdfs_ha_intro.html for a bit more in depth info ", "id": "e59n1uh", "replies": []}], "title": "ELI5: What exactly does Apache Zookeeper do and why is it needed in the Hadoop ecosystem"}